content: This is the best anchor alarm there is. The people who have written bad reviews are complete idiots. Not all devices are equal, people who have had GPS issues is by no fault of this app. It is due to their abused rubbish devices. Before blaming the satellites and apps learn how GPS works! Test the reliability and accuracy of the GPS chip and antenna in your device by downloading "GPS satellite viewer" app and learn how your device calculates it's location by the transmissions received from satel

Without a bearing you have no idea where your anchor is except distance from it. Too much to list probs

I'm a very experienced sailor and have been using this app for over a year.  I think that it's excellent!   I use the 'basic functions' of the app, and haven't messed with the messaging features.     My approach to using the app is pretty straightforward in that every time I drop the anchor I'll 'set the Anchor Watch Pro either by using the "current location" at the moment I lower the anchor, or the 'advanced' location feature if I've already paid out my rode.  One really fantastic thing that you can do with this app is to use it to check the 'set' of your anchor.   So, after you have deployed your anchor and let out  a sufficient amount of rode/scope  then back down on your anchor to be see that it's holding.   I have a catamaran and will put both engines in reverse at about 1/2 cruising RPM.   While doing this I keep an eye on the app and look at the "distance from anchor" number and, once the tension is fully on the anchor, that distance number should not change much.   I've had many occasions in which this little 'feature' of the app has saved me a lot of potential grief because it quickly showed that my anchor was moving.  Highly recommended!!

A very good app but a question regarding the latest version - why is the app now requesting access to photos and files on my phone?
replyContent: The application requests access to files on the phone in order to support custom alarm tones. They are read from phone's storage, that's why this permission is needed. For any other support questions, please email us at support@peckish-sloth.com where it's easier for us to provide longer and more detailed response.

content: Used it first the other night on a slightly dodgy anchorage.  It woke me up following a wind change which was ideal and gave me the confidence to relax! Used this rather than my chart plotter due to its very low power consumption on my Samsung tablet.

I've tried a few anchor alarm programs and this is the best of them IMHO. It has been flawless. We spent last night at a mooring with the wind at 25 knots and this app running all night (after all, how can you completely trust a mooring without diving on it?). I slept well.  Update: it just keeps getting better with every new version!

I was planning to leave an android phone on my boat at anchor while camping on the beach and having it send sms messages to my phone on the beach.   This App is designed perfectly for it but my phone will not update the gps position after about 10-30 minutes.  I was hoping the that by tightening all the screws on the back of the phone the  antenna connection (pressure connection) would fix this issue.  It added accuracy to the GPS but did not fix my problem.  App is perfect but I am not sure whether it is the APP or the phone that is causing the APP not to receive GPS fixes after about 10-30 minutes.  The APP deserves five stars but since I could not get it to work on my phone I gave it four stars.

My favorite anchor alarm yet.  It runs in the background so the screen can sleep.  I run it on my cell phone and the battery lasts all night.  I know i sleep better when its on.  Places for improvement: the option to set the anchor using lat and long, the option to set the anchor from the map with a click and drag.  The ability to play with the swing arc by click and drag from the map.  If its possible, be able to select a 4th type of map layout from a chart plotter app.  Thanks for this great app.

Alarm plays very quiet if you have your phone playing music through a Bluetooth stereo. Alarm should have an option to play through phone speakers always or should at least default to always play at full volume.  Even if I turn the music down on the phone the alarm is fairly quiet.  Clearly the best looking app and very easy to use.  But the alarm being obvious is important.
Was a great app until I transferred to new samsung s7 active.   Program crashes after launch.   Does it work with marshmallow?
replyContent: It has been tested on our devices with Marshmallow. We suggest you try removing the application data and/or manually enabling permissions from settings.

We used the Lite version for a while and then upgraded to Pro, mostly for the location logging. This really helps determine definitively if you have dragged or monitor wind shifts for example while waiting out a cold front. However, you can't leave it on for too long or it runs out of memory and the app crashes. Then you have to uninstall and reinstall, and if you're without wifi/data as is often the case when anchoring, then it's back to using Lite. I try to reset daily to avoid this but sometimes forget.
replyContent: We have published new version of the application that has improved location logging. It stores compressed data so you should now not run out of memory.

content: When putting  out the anchor, I am too busy to think about setting the anchor alarm on my phone but with this app, you can accurately set the alarm after the fact. It works great. This program let's me see in real time how far the anchor drags before it sets or if it does not set at all. I now sleep well knowing this alarm will sound if my anchor starts to move.
